{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2011}} {{Infobox caste |caste_name = Kuruba |religions = [[Hinduism]] |region = [[South India]] |populated_states = [[Karnataka]], [[Andhra Pradesh]], [[Telangana]], [[Tamil Nadu]] and [[Maharashtra]]. |languages = [[Kannada language|Kannada]], [[Telugu language|Telugu]], [[Marathi language|Marathi]] }}
'''Kuruba''' (also known as '''Kuruba Gowda'''<ref name="Kuruba Gowda community">{{cite news|url=https://www.ndtv.com/karnataka-news/in-karnataka-assembly-elections-2018-congress-pitches-chief-minister-siddaramaiah-against-bjps-bs-ye-1706424 |title=In Karnataka Assembly Elections 2018, Congress Pitches Chief Minister Siddaramaiah Against BJP's BS Yeddyurappa |work=NDTV |date=2017-06-01 |accessdate=2018-01-12}}</ref>, '''Kuruba''', '''Kuruma''' and '''Kurumbar''') is a [[Hindu]] [[Caste system in India|caste]] native to the Indian state of [[Karnataka]], where it is the third largest caste group.<ref>[http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-karnataka/kuruba-community-sets-a-new-trend-at-math/article3089204.ece Kuruba community sets a new trend at math]</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://bangaloremirror.indiatimes.com/bangalore/civic//articleshow/44927686.cms |title=Vokkaliga, Lingayat leaders oppose state’s caste census |work=Bangalore Mirror |date=2014-10-25 |accessdate=2018-01-12}}</ref> Like [[Yadav]]a and [[Dhangar]], the community's traditional occupation was [[shepherd]]ing.<ref name="RCDhere_Vitthal">{{cite book |url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=jUeeAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA256 | title=Rise of a Folk God: Vitthal of Pandharpur, South Asia Research | publisher=Oxford University Press, | author=Ramchandra Chintaman Dhere, Translated by [[Anne Feldhaus]] | year=2011 | pages=240-241 | isbn=9780199777648}}</ref> <ref name="Encyclopedia of Religions">{{cite book | url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=O_OviUJRzJAC&pg=PA50 | title=Encyclopedia of Religions | publisher=Cosimo, Inc., | author=John G. R. Forlong | year=2008 | page=50 | isbn=9781605204840}}</ref>
==Etymology== The term ''kuruba'', meaning ''shepherd'', is derived from ''kuri'', meaning ''sheep''.<ref name="RCDhere_Vitthal"/>
==History== The Kurubas are said to have been connected to the [[Yadu]] or [[Yadava]] lineage mentioned in [[Purana]]s. Traditional sources claim that the Kurubas founded the [[Sangama Dynasty|Sangama dynasty]] and the [[Vijayanagara Empire]].<ref name="The YadavasGod">{{cite book |url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=jUeeAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA243 |title=Rise of a Folk God: Vitthal of Pandharpur, South Asia Research |publisher=Oxford University Press, |first=Ramchandra Chintaman |last=Dhere |authorlink=Ramchandra Chintaman Dhere |others=Feldhaus, Anne (trans.) |year=2011 |page=243 |isbn=978-0-19977-764-8}}</ref>
According to [[Ramchandra Chintaman Dhere]], a scholar of the religious traditions of Maharashtra, {{quote|The history of South India shows clearly that all the southern royal dynasties who arose from pastoralist, cowherd groups gained Kshatriya status by claiming to be Moon lineage Kshatriya, by taking Yadu as their ancestor and by continually keeping alive their pride in being "Yadava". Many dynasties in South India from the Pallavas to Yadurayas were originally members of pastoralist, cowherd groups and belonged to Kuruba lineages.<ref name="The YadavasGod"/>}}
