The '''Thai Zig zag scam''' is a [[confidence trick]] where one is falsely accused of shoplifting, and then held by police, or those claiming to be police, until "bail" is paid for the alleged theft. At times those fleeced are shown faked [[closed-circuit television]] footage as corroboration. In several cases in Thailand, this confidence trick has occurred at the airport, and thus is sometimes called the "Thai airport scam". Most reports of this scam are dated.<ref>{{cite news |title=Duty free shop 'theft' scam a case of recycled news |url=http://www.nationmultimedia.com/detail/aec/30325091 |accessdate=15 October 2018 |work=The Nation |agency=Asia News Network |date=2017-08-28}}</ref>
==Cases== According to the BBC, police in Bangkok's [[Suvarnabhumi Airport]] have participated in a series of these scams, robbing tourists of thousands of dollars each time.<ref name="BBC-20090720">{{cite news |last1=Head |first1=Jonathan |title=Tourists warned of Thailand airport scam |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/8154497.stm |accessdate=15 October 2018 |work=BBC News |date=20 July 2009}}</ref> A British couple was charged with stealing a wallet.<ref name="BBC-20090720"/> The Thai embassy in Singapore published a rebuttal to the BBC article, stating that all legal proceedings in the case of the Britons were conducted "...in accordance with the law."<ref>{{cite web |title=Facts about the alleged Thailand airport scam |url=https://www.thaiembassy.sg/announcements/facts-about-the-alleged-thailand-airport-scam |website=Royal Thai Embassy Singapore |accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref> An Irish woman was charged with stealing eye-liner.<ref name="BBC-20090720"/> An Australian man was charged with stealing a doughnut.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.news.com.au/travel/story/0,28318,25525480-5014090,00.html |title=News.com.au:Sydney school teacher Sean Kearney accused of stealing doughnut in Thailand |access-date=2009-08-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090525202932/http://www.news.com.au/travel/story/0,28318,25525480-5014090,00.html |archive-date=2009-05-25 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
